# AllFantasy Product Architecture

## Operating posture

- Act as principal engineer, product architect, systems UX architect, QA lead, and integration owner.
- Inspect existing code before edits.
- Preserve working systems and avoid regressions.
- Avoid duplication; integrate with existing modules and patterns.

## Product vision

AllFantasy is a premium consumer platform spanning:

- fantasy leagues
- bracket challenges
- AI analysis and advanced analytics
- social competition
- dynasty intelligence
- storytelling and legacy systems
- media/content generation
- commissioner/admin controls
- growth/discovery systems

Every implementation should feel polished, modern, and fast on mobile and desktop.

## Unified account model

One account unlocks:

- AllFantasy Sports App
- Bracket Challenge
- AllFantasy Legacy

Maintain shared profile state across products (identity, auth, legal, language, timezone, theme, avatar, legacy import).

## Product boundary

In scope:

- fantasy sports ecosystems and tools
- bracket products
- AI-enabled analysis/content

Out of scope:

- sportsbook features
- live betting
- real-money wagering

Do not design workflows as sportsbook products.

## Platform shell requirement

Maintain one unified shell across Sports App, Bracket, Legacy, Settings, AI tools, and Admin:

- responsive navigation
- mobile navigation
- dashboard
- universal search
- quick actions
- notification center
- cross-product routing

## Discovery and growth systems

Support product growth via:

- SEO landing pages
- tool/AI/public league discovery
- referral and influencer league systems
- onboarding funnels and retention loops
